#  KU Bookstore improvements
  
* Streamline payment process, offer multiple payment methods
* In-Text book search
* KU merchandize simulated preview, based on student image
* Technical advice that fits your major. 
   * So you get individual advice what laptop etc. you should buy after entering your major and other information (the system checks what your needs are and finds solutions that fits that requirements..) -> basically computer scientist need higher performance than e.g. history students
* Ticket Sales
   * Events and games
* Student discount hub for restaurants and various partners. 
* Virtual library
   * Students join working groups and have an exchange on many different topics 
* Outdoor pickup system (due to covid)
   * Signup online, currently long lines
 * Price matching service
 * Buy back improvements included
 * Tech shop improvements?
